// Russell paradox / "Type : Type" self-typing tests.
//
// Per TYPE_THEORY.typ §5.5: the universe is structurally Russell-admissible
// — Type recognises itself (and every other predicate-frame type-former)
// without rank stratification. This file pins that observation across the
// core type-formers.
//
// ================================================================
// Russell paradox itself — NOT TESTABLE in current framework
// ================================================================
//
// The full Russell paradox term is something like:
//
//     R := {T} -> not (T T)
//     R R   // should diverge — R R = not (R R) is unsatisfiable
//
// In a `Type : Type` system without paradox-blocking machinery this term
// is expected to diverge (no normal form). The current test framework
// compares hash-cons identity at compile time and has no BudgetExhausted
// recovery — running `test R R = ...` would hang the entire test run.
//
// Future test-harness requirement: a budget-controlled "diverges" assertion
// (e.g., `test_diverges R R` runs N reduction steps, succeeds if non-normal,
// fails if a normal form is reached). Until that lands, Russell-the-paradox
// remains a documented expectation, not an executed test.

open use "../prelude.disp"
open use "../kernel/prelude.disp"

// ================================================================
// H-rule self-typing — Type contains itself
// ================================================================
// Type recognises any guarded predicate_frame wait-form. Type itself
// is built exactly that way, so `Type Type = TT`.

test Type Type = TT
test Type Type_pf = TT
test Type_pf Type = TT

// ================================================================
// Core library type-formers qualify as Types
// ================================================================

test Type Bool = TT
test Type Nat = TT
test Type Ord = TT
test Type (Pi Nat ({_} -> Nat)) = TT
test Type (Pi Bool ({_} -> Nat)) = TT
test Type (Pi Type ({A} -> Arrow A A)) = TT
test Type (Arrow Nat Bool) = TT
test Type False = TT

// Eq is now predicate_frame (post-migration); qualifies as a Type.
test Type (Eq Nat 0 0) = TT
test Type (Eq Nat 0 1) = TT

// ================================================================
// Closed values are NOT types
// ================================================================
// Concrete inhabitants (Nat literals, Bool literals, refl) lack the
// guarded predicate_frame structure, so the recognizer says FF.

test Type 5 = FF
test Type 0 = FF
test Type TT = FF
test Type FF = FF
test Type refl = FF
test Type t = FF
test Type (t t) = FF
test Type (t t t) = FF

// ================================================================
// Public-boundary hypothesis rejection
// ================================================================
// Public Type still scans for pre-existing neutrals at the boundary,
// so a Type-typed hypothesis is rejected even though it's semantically
// "of type Type". (H-rule fires only through the inner core, which
// type_pf.test.disp already exercises.)

let type_hyp = Hyp Type 0
test Type type_hyp = FF
